Kim Jong Il Greets Nong Duc Manh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Nong Duc Manh, Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam, arrived in Pyongyang by a special plane on Oct. 16 to pay an official goodwill visit to the DPRK at the invitation of Kim Jong Il, General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il greeted Nong Duc Manh at the Pyongyang Airport. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thousands of Pyongyangites turned out to the airport with flags of the two countries and flowers in their hands to greet the envoys of Vietnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the airport were Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Yong Il, premier of the Cabinet, Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, Kim Jong Gak, first vice director of the General Political Bureau of the Korean People's Army, Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the SPA Presidium, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Kang Sok Ju, first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, leading officials of the party and power organs, ministries and national institutions and Ma Chol Su, DPRK ambassador to Vietnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK, and staff members of the Vietnamese embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At 2 p.m. the plane carrying the goodwill envoys of the Vietnamese people touched down at the airport. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il exchanged a firm handshake with Nong Duc Manh and warmly hugged him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arriving here together with Nong Duc Manh were Pham Gia Khiem, member of the Political Bureau of the C.C., the Communist Party of Vietnam who is also deputy prime minister and foreign minister, and Tran Van Hang, chairman of the Commission for External Affairs of the Party Central Committee, Ngo Van Du, chief of the General Office of the Party Central Committee, Hoang Tuan Anh, minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism, who are members of the Party Central Committee, and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A function took place at the airport in welcome of Nong Duc Manh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il and Nong Duc Manh reviewed the guard of honor of the KPA three services amid the booming of a 21-gun salute. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A woman worker presented a bouquet carrying friendly feelings to Nong Duc Manh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Women of the Vietnamese embassy here presented fragrant bouquets to Kim Jong Il and Nong Duc Manh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nong Duc Manh waved back to the enthusiastically cheering crowd, walking past them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His visit to the DPRK is a manifestation of the firm support and solidarity to the Korean people in their just cause of building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieving the independent and peaceful reunification of the country and marks an important occasion in boosting the friendly relations between the DPRK and Vietnam.

Pyongyangites Warmly Welcome Nong Duc Manh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- A large number of Pyongyangites warmly welcomed along the route Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam Nong Duc Manh, who came here Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The limousine carrying Nong Duc Manh and Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, passed through Kum Song Street after leaving the entrance of Ryonmot-dong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A woman worker presented a bouquet to the secretary general at the entrance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Children's Union offered salutes to the secretary general, presented him with bouquets and put a tie of the Children's Union around his neck at the square in front of the April 25 House of Culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The crowd warmly welcomed the Vietnamese friends along the route, waving flags of the two countries and bunches of flowers.

Nong Duc Manh Pays Homage to Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Nong Duc Manh, Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam, visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace, the supreme temple of Juche, on Tuesday to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Visitors to the palace included Pham Gia Khiem, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam who is also deputy prime minister and foreign minister, and other suite members and Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Pak Kyong Son, vice department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and Ma Chol Su, DPRK ambassador to Vietnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket in the name of Nong Duc Manh was placed before the statue of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the floral basket were letters "President Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people, will live forever".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nong Duc Manh paid homage to Kim Il Sung, who made immortal contribution to the development of the friendly relations between the two countries and the two parties, in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He went round with deep emotion the orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles the President received from the DPRK and different countries of the world, the Mourning Hall and a train coach and car used by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nong Duc Manh wrote in the visitor's book that President Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people and great friend of the Vietnamese people, together with respected President Ho Chi Minh of the Vietnamese people provided a solid foundation for the friendship between Vietnam and the DPRK, adding that Kim Il Sung will always live with the revolutionary cause of the Korean people and the Vietnam-DPRK friendship.

Talks Held between Kim Yong Nam and Nong Duc Manh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Talks were held between Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, and Nong Duc Manh, Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Pak Ui Chun, minister of Foreign Affairs, Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture, Ma Chol Su, DPRK ambassador to Vietnam, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present from the Vietnamese side were Pham Gia Khiem, member of the Political Bureau of the Party Central Committee who is also deputy prime minister and foreign minister, and Tran Van Hang, chairman of the Commission for External Affairs of the Party Central Committee, Ngo Van Du, chief of the General Office of the Party Central Committee, and Hoang Tuan Anh, minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism, who are members of the Party Central Committee, Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK, and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.

Banquet Given for Nong Duc Manh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea hosted a banquet at the Mokran House Tuesday in honor of Nong Duc Manh, Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation together with Nong Duc Manh were Pham Gia Khiem, member of the Political Bureau of the C.C., the Communist Party of Vietnam who is also deputy prime minister and foreign minister, and Tran Van Hang, chairman of the Commission for External Affairs of the Party Central Committee, Ngo Van Du, chief of the General Office of the Party Central Committee, and Hoang Tuan Anh, minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism, who are members of the Party Central Committee, Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK, and other suite members and members of the Vietnamese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Pak Nam Gi and Ri Kwang Ho, department directors of the WPK Central Committee, Pak Ui Chun, foreign minister, Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture, Ma Chol Su, DPRK ambassador to Vietnam, and leading officials of party, armed forces and power organs, ministries and national institutions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam made a speech at the banquet. He said that the Vietnamese people are now steadily advancing socialism as intended by President Ho Chi Minh despite the intensified moves of the imperialists and reactionaries and striving to enhance the influence and position of the country in the international arena under the leadership of the Communist Party of Vietnam headed by Secretary General Nong Duc Manh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK and the Korean people follow this with deep attention and sincerely wish the Vietnamese people greater success in the work to implement the decision of the 10th Congress of the Communist Party of Vietnam and realize the industrialization and modernization of the country at an early date, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the common aspiration of the two peoples at present to develop the friendly relations between the two parties and two countries based on the particular comradely bonds of the revolutionary forerunners as required by the new century, he said, expressing the belief that the friendly relations between the two parties and two countries would grow stronger thanks to their joint efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nong Duc Manh spoke next. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the sincere thanks of the Vietnamese people to the fraternal Korean party, government and people for supporting and encouraging the struggle for the independence, freedom and reunification of the country in the past period and the present cause of building and defending Vietnam, the socialist country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We always set store by the traditional relations of friendship and cooperation between the two parties, two countries and two peoples of Vietnam and the DPRK personally provided by President Ho Chi Minh and President Kim Il Sung and give assurances that we will make every effort to steadily consolidate and develop them, he noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vietnam has consistently supported the desire of the Korean people for the peaceful reunification of the country and hails the recent progress made at the six-party talks and the results of the second meeting of the top leaders of the north and the south of Korea. And it is ready to positively contribute to promoting peace, stability and cooperation on the Korean Peninsula and supports the expansion of cooperation between the DPRK and ASEAN and its member nations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We highly appreciate the results of the current high-level talks between Vietnam and the DPRK and believe that the traditional relations of friendship and cooperation between the two parties, two countries and two peoples of Vietnam and the DPRK would enter into a new phase of stable, realistic and effective development thanks to the efforts of both sides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The banquet took place in a friendly atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  An art performance was given by the State Merited Chorus of the Korean People's Army at the banquet.

Papers Welcome Goodwill Envoy of Vietnamese People 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Newspapers here today editorially welcome Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam Nong Duc Manh arriving in Pyongyang today on an official goodwill visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visit of the goodwill envoy of the Vietnamese people to the DPRK constitutes support and encouragement to the Korean people in their just struggle for socialism and national reunification and marks a great event in strengthening and developing the DPRK-Vietnam friendly relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bilateral friendly relations are based on the comradely relationship which President Kim Il Sung forged with Ho Chi Minh, respected leader of the Vietnamese people, and have developed on good terms on the basis of them. The peoples of the two countries waged an arduous and difficult joint struggle against the imperialist aggressors, their common enemy, sharing intentions and will. Over the past years the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation have grown strong in the course of carrying out the common cause of building socialism against the imperialist aggressors, making contributions to promoting the revolution and construction in the two countries and ensuring peace and security in Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Vietnam friendly relations have now entered a new phase of development. The visit of the president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly to Vietnam and the visit of the president of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam to the DPRK in recent years marked important occasions in developing the bilateral friendly relations onto a higher stage as required by the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Vietnamese people are defending and advancing socialism chosen by them under the leadership of the Communist Party of Vietnam headed by Nong Duc Manh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the peoples of the two countries are supporting and solidarizing with each other in their causes, the paper says that the DPRK visit of the secretary general of the C.C., the Communist Party of Vietnam will record a new chapter in the history of the DPRK-Vietnam friendship and go a long way towards promoting the socialist cause and the movement for global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that firm is the will of the Workers' Party of Korea and the government of the DPRK to develop the friendly and cooperative relations with the Vietnamese people and thus promote the co-prosperity and common interests of the peoples of the two countries and achieve peace and development in Asia.

Thae Jong Su Appointed as Vice-Premier of DPRK Cabinet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Thae Jong Su was appointed as vice-premier of the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A decree of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly in this regard was promulgated on Tuesday.

DPRK, Egypt Cooperate in Culture 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- A 2007-2009 plan for implementing the agreement on cultural cooperation between the governments of the DPRK and Egypt was signed in Cairo on Oct. 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the signing ceremony from the DPRK side were members of the government cultural delegation headed by Jon Hyon Chan, vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and the DPRK ambassador to Egypt and from the Egyptian side an ambassador of the Egyptian Foreign Ministry and other officials concerned.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Foreigner
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the head of the visiting delegation of the International Kim Il Sung Foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to an official concerned Tuesday by Johnny Hon, chairman of the foundation who is leading the delegation and also chairman of the Global Group of Britain.

DPRK Team Wins Title of 2007 Asian Women's U-19 Football Championships
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- The DPRK team trounced its Japanese rival 1:0 in the finals of the 2007 Asian Women's U-19 Football Championships held in China on October 16, winning the title of the championships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was qualified to participate in the FIFA U-20 Women's World Championships to be held in Chile in 2008.

Sinuiju School for Disabled Soldiers, Centre for Training Native Cadres 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) --Sinuiju School for Disabled Soldiers in North Phyongan Province, the DPRK has covered a proud road of development over last 50 odd years since its institution. It has trained disabled soldiers into native cadres. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Busy as he was with the work of leading the Fatherland Liberation War to a brilliant victory, President Kim Il Sung saw to it that a school for disabled soldiers who devotedly fought for the country and people was established on July 1, Juche 40 (1951) and directed close attention to it at all times.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called at the then Disabled Soldiers Industrial School No. 1 on June 21, 1952 despite a rain of shells and powder smoke. He said that disabled soldiers that they should live an optimistic life and study hard with the spirit with which they fought on the front to become dependable native cadres. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise leadership and warm care of the Workers' Party of Korea and the leader, the school has developed into a college-standard educational institution which trains disabled soldiers into cadres who are sound politically and ideologically and prepared scientifically and technically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The school with a house of culture, comprehensive welfare service facilities and supply base provides students with excellent living conditions. The students get regular medical examination and treatment at the school clinic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The students are supplied with the school uniforms according to seasons and daily necessities from the state free of charge while studying in the school.  The graduates of the school are doing much toward the prosperity of the country and the improvement of the people's living as functionaries of party and government bodies, economic organs and industrial establishments.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Tuesday dedicates an article to the 25th publication anniversary of Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Workers' Party of Korea Is a Juche-Type Revolutionary Party Which Inherited the Glorious Tradition of the DIU".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work serves as an important document as it comprehensively deals with theoretical and practical problems arising in steadily adding shine to the glorious history and tradition of the WPK which has covered a unique path under the banner of the Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DIU represents the roots of the WPK, the origin of Songun and a model of unity, the author of the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the great tradition of the DIU the WPK has grown to be an experienced and tested invincible revolutionary party, the army of the DPRK has been built into a matchless army and the Party, army and people are single-mindedly rallied close around the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK which inherited the glorious tradition of the DIU is a dignified revolutionary party holding aloft the banner of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historical experience goes to prove that if a party fails to maintain independence, it can never ensure consistency in party building and activities nor creditably carry out its historical mission as a political guiding organization of the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK is a revolutionary party winning one victory after another under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics of the WPK originated from the DIU. The banner of the DIU was a banner of Songun, banner of the most vigorous struggle against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK is a powerful revolutionary party holding high the banner of single-minded unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One of the greatest feats performed by the DIU was that it gave origin to the unity of revolutionary ranks around the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK has become an ideologically pure party as all its members are replete with the Juche-based Songun idea and the spirit of devotedly defending the leader. And it has become elite ranks in which all members act as one in accordance with the intentions of the leader and fully display the spirit of devotedly implementing them. This is the true picture of the WPK, faithful inheritor of the tradition of unity of the DIU.

World Food Day Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Today marks the founding anniversary of the UN Food and Agricultural Organization and the World Food Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun in a signed article dedicated to the day says that the purpose of instituting the World Food Day was to bring the importance of the food problem home to the people of all countries and intensify international discussion on the urgency of solution to the food problem worldwide and the ways of solving it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theme of the World Food Day this year is the "right to food". The acute food shortage worldwide adversely affects humankind in enjoying this right. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The worldwide solution to the food problem is by no means impossible. If all the countries of the world buckle down to the problem they can surely solve it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many countries have exerted much effort for developing agriculture so as to solve the food problem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has waged a dynamic drive to boost agricultural production despite natural disasters that hit the country for several consecutive years. It has taken a series of realistic and effective measures to solve the food problem. It has strictly abided by the principle of right crop on the right soil and right crop in the right time and introducing advanced farming technique and method while pushing forward such large scale nature-remaking projects as land realignment and waterway projects under a detailed plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Big progress can be made in solving the world food problem if each country and people make positive efforts to increase grain production and strengthen international cooperation and exchange.

WPK Birthday Marked in Venezuela
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- A function for laying a floral basket before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il took place at the head office of the Communist Party of Venezuela on Oct. 8 to mark the 62nd anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Venezuela and members of the leadership of the party.  After placing the floral basket the participants paid tribute to them.

WPK Praised in Foreign Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Bangladesh and the Bangladesh National Socialist Party issued a joint statement on October 9 on the occasion of the 62nd anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement noted that it is of particular significance for the world progressives to celebrate the 62nd birthday of the WPK, expressing the firm belief that the WPK led by Kim Jong Il would continue to make a victorious advance, frustrating any moves of the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Indian political figures also made public statements on this occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Palam Sen Gupta, secretary of the National Council of the Communist Party of India, said in a statement issued on Oct. 8 that the Korean people are dynamically advancing along the road of victory despite all sorts of difficulties under the banner of socialism and independence against imperialism, adding that the WPK always stands in the van of the struggle of the brave Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK which was founded by President Kim Il Sung has grown to be an experienced and tested party leading the people to victory in any storm and ordeal and a popular party enjoying support and trust of the Korean people through a protracted struggle, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harising Khang, member of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of India (Marxist), said in a statement on Oct. 9 that over the past more than six decades the WPK has always led the struggle of the Korean people for socialist construction and national reunification along the road of victory, holding high the banner of the Juche idea, the banner of Songun.

Kim Jong Il's Work Posted on Internet Theoretical Magazine
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy and the U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics posted on Internet theoretical magazine "Red Flag of Songun" Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" on October 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on October 2, Juche 84(1995), is an immortal great programme for party building and activities as it reviews with pride the glorious history of the WPK, which paved a new way for building a revolutionary party in the era of independence under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung, and clearly indicates the road of strengthening and developing the WPK into the eternal party of the President.

Kim Jong Il recibe a Nong Duc Manh
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 16 de octubre (ATCC) -- Arribo este martes a esta capital en un avion especial el secretario general del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de Vietnam, Nong Duc Manh, para realizar una visita oficial y de amistad a la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea cumplimentando la invitacion del Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente acogio al huesped en el Aeropuerto de Pyongyang, donde estaban conglomerados miles de capitalinos portando banderitas de los dos paises y ramos de flores para dar bienvenida a los visitantes vietnamitas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Alli estaban el presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema Kim Yong Nam, el primer ministro del Consejo de Ministros Kim Yong Il, el ministro de las Fuerzas Armadas Populares Kim Il Chol, el primer subjefe de la Direccion Politica General del Ejercito Popular de Corea Kim Jong Gak, el vicepresidente del Presidium de la APS Yang Hyong Sop, el secretario del CC del PTC Kim Ki Nam, el primer vicecanciller Kang Sok Ju, los funcionarios directivos de los organismos del partido y el Poder, ministerios y organos centrales, y el embajador coreano en Vietnam Ma Chol Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tambien se veian el embajador Le Van Cu y otros miembros de la sede diplomatica vietnamita en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A las 2 de la tarde, aterrizo el avion en que viajaba el enviado de amistad del pueblo vietnamita. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente y Nong Duc Manh se abrazaron cordialmente tras un apreton de manos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Acompanaron a Nong Duc Manh el miembro del Buro Politico del CC del PCV, vicepremier del gobierno y canciller, Pham Gia Khiem, los miembros del CC del PCV: Tran van Hang, Ngo Van Du y Hoang Tuan Anh, presidente de la Comision de Relaciones Exteriores del CC del PCV, jefe de la Oficina del CC del PCV y ministro de Cultura, Deporte y Turismo, respectivamente, y otros acompanantes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En el mismo lugar tuvo lugar una ceremonia de bienvenida. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Mientras se disparaban 21 salvas, el Dirigente y el secretario general pasaron revista a la guardia de honor de las fuerzas terrestres, navales y aereas del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Una trabajadora obsequio al visitante un ramo de flores rebosante de sentimiento de amistad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Mujeres de la embajada vietnamita hicieron lo mismo al Dirigente y el visitante. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El segundo respondio con su mano alzada a la multitud, que le daba una calida bienvenida, pasando por delante de ella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Esta visita significa una manifestacion de irrestricto apoyo y solidaridad a la justa causa del pueblo coreano para construir una gran potencia prospera socialista y adelantar la reunificacion independiente y pacifica de Corea y deviene una importante oportunidad para fortalecer y desarrollar las relaciones de amistad entre los dos paises.

Nong Duc Manh rinde homenaje a Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 16 de octubre (ATCC) -- El secretario general del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de Vietnam, Nong Duc Manh, rindio este martes homenaje al Presidente Kim Il Sung en el Palacio Memorial Kumsusan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Lo hicieron tambien el miembro del Buro Politico del CC del PCV, vicepremier del gobierno y canciller, Pham Gia Khiem, y otros acompanantes y el embajador en Corea Le Van Cu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Les acompanaron el presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la RPDC, Kim Yong Nam, el subjefe de departamento del CC del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Pak Kyong Son, y el embajador coreano en Vietnam, Ma Chol Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Fue depositado ante la estatua del Presidente un cesto de flores a nombre del secretario general del CC del PCV. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En su cinta se leia: "Sera inmortal el Presidente Kim Il Sung, gran Lider del pueblo coreano".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Luego, el visitante rindio homenaje al Presidente quien hizo un gran aporte al desarrollo de las relaciones de amistad entre los dos paises y partidos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Acto seguido, recorrio con profunda emocion las ordenes, medallas y titulos honorarios otorgados por Corea y varios paises del mundo otorgados al Presidente, el hall de llantos, el vagon y el auto utilizados por el. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Por ultimo, escribio en el libro de visitas: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@"El Presidente Kim Il Sung, gran lider del pueblo coreano y gran amigo del pueblo vietnamita, sento junto con el respetado presidente del pueblo vietnamita, Ho Chi Minh, la firme base para la amistad Vietnam-Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El sera inmortal junto con la causa revolucionaria del pueblo coreano y el sentimiento de amistad Vietnam-Corea".

Kim Yong Nam conversa con Nong Duc Manh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 16 de octubre (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar este martes en el Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae en un clima amistoso las conversaciones entre el presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam, y el secretario general del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de Vietnam, Nong Duc Manh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion estuvieron presentes por la parte coreana el secretario del CC del Partido del Trabajo de Corea Kim Ki Nam, el viceprimer ministro del Consejo de Ministros Ro Tu Chol, el canciller Pak Ui Chun, el ministro de Cultura Kang Nung Su, el embajador en Vietnam Ma Chol Su y otros funcionarios y por la vietnamita, Pham Gia Khiem, miembro del Buro Politico del CC del PCV, vicepremier del gobierno y canciller, los miembros del CC del PCV: Tran van Hang, Ngo Van Du y Hoang Tuan Anh, presidente de la Comision de Relaciones Exteriores del CC del PCV, jefe de la Oficina del CC del PCV y ministro de Cultura, Deporte y Turismo, respectivamente, el embajador en Corea Le Van Cu y otros acompanantes.
